 we highlight the presence of a\ntimescale $T\\sim e^{c L\\ln L}$ for the decay of a region of large linear size\n$L$. The implications of our work for the classic problem of the decay of a\nfalse vacuum are also discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Sep 2022 13:08:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Jan 2023 15:25:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-24"}
