e range of frequency they cover. We show\nthat indeed a small sensitivity loss may happen in presence of a very high mean\nsignal density affecting a frequency range of the order of one Hertz, while\nwhen the signal cluster covers a frequency range of one tenth of Hertz, or\nless, we may actually have a sensitivity gain. Overall, we demonstrate the FH\nto be robust even in presence of moderate-to-large signal clusters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Sep 2022 15:04:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-20"}
